For 2-3 cups of chaha thinly slice or grate @ginger{5%g}
Optionally you can crush @cardamon{2%pods}.
Add the spices to @water{600ml} and bring to a nice boil.

Simmer the spices until the water has turned slighly green, this can take 3-~{5%min}.

With the water simmering add @black tea{2.5%tsp} and boild for ~{2%min}. 

Add @sugar{2%tsp} and @milk{150%ml}. Stir and bring twice to a boil.

Use a strainer and serve into 2-3 mugs.
